This project is a faithful port of Fast-TRELLIS's training-free acceleration
method onto microsoft/TRELLIS.2. It bundles and/or adapts code from the
following MIT-licensed third-party projects. All credit for the original work
belongs to their respective authors.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
microsoft/TRELLIS.2
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Copyright (c) Microsoft Corporation.
Licensed under the MIT License.
https://github.com/microsoft/TRELLIS.2
https://huggingface.co/microsoft/TRELLIS.2-4B

The base image-to-3D model, pipeline, samplers, sparse modules, renderers and
representations under trellis2/ are from TRELLIS.2 and remain under Microsoft's
copyright and the MIT License.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Fast-TRELLIS (wlfeng0509/Fast-TRELLIS)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Copyright (c) wlfeng0509.
Licensed under the MIT License.
https://github.com/wlfeng0509/Fast-TRELLIS

The training-free acceleration method (TaylorSeer sparse-structure cache,
SLaT easy delta-cache with learned-k skip, and token carving) is from
Fast-TRELLIS. The util packages taylor_utils_ss/, faster_utils_slat/,
token_slat/ and fft/, and the *_taylor / *_faster sampler classes in
trellis2/pipelines/samplers/flow_euler.py, are a faithful port of that method
to TRELLIS.2 (v1 -> v2). This repository replicates their contribution.
